                                                <p>After breakfast, depart for city tour to visit Notre Dame Cathedral was built between 1877 and 1883 and the stone used to create it was exported in its entirety from France. Next to the cathedral stands the Central Post Office, finished in 1891. It is another fine example of French architecture and is Vietnam's largest post office. Continue to visit the Reunification Palace was the former residence of the President of South Vietnam until April 30, 1975. End half day tour with a stroll around the bustling Ben Thanh Market - a fantastic place for shopping then transfer to Tan Son Nhat airport to take flight to Hoi An. Upon arrival pick-up by our private guide and transfer to Hoi An for overnight.</p>
